><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>&#8220;It was the shortest path from inspiration=
 to output that I&#8217;ve ever seen,&#8221; </strong><span>he noted.&#160;=
</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>While all of this was happening, Dancho =
&amp; Jos&#233; thought the a16z deal was dead, because a16z said they want=
ed to see more game film. It was fine &#8211; they weren&#8217;t raising, t=
hey didn&#8217;t </span><em>need </em><span>the money &#8211; they just did=
n&#8217;t think it was happening.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54=
, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">&#8220;=
A few days after they passed &#8211; 12 days after that,&#8221; Dancho reco=
unted:&#160;</p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #0c2427; margin=
: 20px 0; padding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px;=
 line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em><span>We ge=
t an email from Anish saying, something like, &#8220;Hey guys, I&#8217;ve b=
een using your app for the past week, I&#8217;m obsessed, want to make some=
thing happen.&#8221; He fully apologized. </span><strong>&#8220;I&#8217;ve =
never done this where I passed and wanted to make something happen, but I&#=
8217;m in love with your app and want to make something happen.&#8221;</str=
ong></em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Then he made something ha=
ppen. </span><strong>a16z led an $18 million Series A.</strong></p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">Which is a fun thing to be able to say about a portfolio company,=
 but really, is the money Dancho, Jos&#233;, and their absurdly small 7-per=
son team need to start building down the stack.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">=
Because sitting at the &#8220;top of the Musical Creator Stack&#8221; is ju=
st the right entry point to go further down, to &#8220;vertically integrate=
 the entire music stack for artists.&#8221;&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb=
(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Reme=
mber, though, when Adam said that it wasn&#8217;t clear if that was even te=
chnically possible?&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size:=
 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">&#8220;You need to ask them =
to see the latest design,&#8221; he told me. &#8220;It&#8217;s an extremely=
 feature-rich product designed in a way that doesn&#8217;t feel overwhelmin=
g at all. I don&#8217;t know how they&#8217;ve done it.&#8221;&#160;</p><p =
style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin=
: 0 0 20px 0;">Of course, Adam is an [untitled] investor. He&#8217;s suppos=
ed to say nice things for public consumption. But he also said it wasn&#821=
7;t always like this.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-siz=
e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">&#8220;There was a long pe=
riod where it was extremely frustrating,&#8221; he told me. &#8220;They tre=
ated the product like a Faberge Egg that they didn&#8217;t want to break. T=
hey didn&#8217;t want to get it into the hands of users to tell them it suc=
ked.&#8221; Adam, Mo, and Niko had to push Dancho &amp; Jos&#233; into the =
deep end: &#8220;You need to ship faster and you need to get user feedback =
in tighter loops because development cycles aren&#8217;t happening quickly =
enough.&#8221;&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">There&#8217;s always that tension=
, in music, between art and capital. The artist wants it to be perfect. The=
 capitalist wants it to make money. It&#8217;s clear talking to Dancho &amp=
; Jos&#233;, and hearing these stories, that they lean artist. Which is pro=
bably why the product is so damn good in an age when most apps kind of suck=
=2E&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54,=20=
55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But once again, you need money to make the art=
, and you need crowds to tell you if it&#8217;s any good.&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">So they listened. This is the back half of 2023. And they put the=
 product in musicians&#8217; hands, afraid that they were going to have the=
ir feelings hurt, and &#8230; they didn&#8217;t. Musicians loved it. They r=
ealized they built something that people actually wanted, lots of people. T=
hey combined the artists&#8217; sensitivity with the capitalists&#8217; spe=
ed, and tightened that craft, ship, iterate loop, and that&#8217;s why, in =
the spring of 2024, the product was growing fast enough and gaining enough =
popularity &#8211; even among the big time artists backing the Cultural Lea=
dership Fund &#8211; that a16z took notice and wrote them a check.&#160;</p=
><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 20px 0;">Which is why they can build more of the OS, now, which D=
ancho showed me the other day.&#160;</p><h3 class=3D"header-anchor-post" st=
yle=3D"--highlight-bg: rgba(var(--color-bg-accent-themed-rgb), 0.2); -moz-a=
ppearance: optimizelegibility; -moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webki=
