t, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', '=
Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; =
line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0; position: relative;"><strong>=
The Operating System for Music</strong></h3><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, =
55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">&#8220;We&#82=
17;re not ready to show this to a lot of people yet,&#8221; Dancho warned, =
&#8220;but I&#8217;ll show you what we have.&#8221;&#160;</p><p style=3D"co=
lor: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px =
0;">Describing the app in words is, at best, like trying to get you to appr=
eciate a song by reading you the lyrics in monotone. Maybe I&#8217;ll start=
 with some OS philosophy, which does work in words.</p><p style=3D"color: r=
gb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">&#=
8220;If you think about an Operating System&#8221; &#8211; this is how Danc=
ho started the demo, and I think gives a hint as to why this team is so goo=
d at product &#8211; &#8220;It has a bunch of different apps that do the di=
fferent things you need.&#8221;</p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px so=
lid #0c2427; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55=
